}{}$\mu \text {g/m}^{3}$
\end{document} (33%). A 20.4% to 55.5% reduction in NO2 during full and partial lockdown scenario, respectively, compared to the pre-COVID situation, was also reported in Dhaka, Bangladesh [102]. Thus, it is evidenced that the concentration of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
